This paper focuses on optimizing the runtime performance of applying tree-based models, which is a common problem in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses data structures and execution flow, which are relevant to data structures (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper explores architecture-conscious runtime implementations, which is relevant to computer architecture (cs.AR).
